  "commentary": "Dealers are currently caught in active hedging mode with SPX at 7029.8 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7015 (where they buy dips) and the massive positive gamma wall at 7050 (where they sell rallies). The recent \"wall_break\" event combined with the -2.3% 1-min move suggests we just punched through a key level, but the strong positive gamma structure above should provide natural resistance and pull price back toward the 7030-7035 zone. Watch for dealer selling pressure to intensify if we push toward 7050, while any dip toward 7015 should see aggressive dealer buying support.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get squeezed back toward 7030 with limited upside past 7050.",
